edu.umn.biomedicus.numbers

Class CombinedNumberDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umn.biomedicus.numbers.CombinedNumberDetector

  • public class CombinedNumberDetector
extends Object
    Detects both decimal numbers using DecimalNumberAcceptor and english numbers using EnglishNumeralsAcceptor.

    It is not safe to use an instance of this class from multiple threads at once, use multiple instances for concurrency.

    Since:
    1.0.0

      • tryToken

        public boolean tryToken(String token,
                        int tokenBegin,
                        int tokenEnd)
        Passes the number detector the specified token, seeing if it has detected a number from the tokens that this instance has received.
        Parameters:
        token - the token to check
        tokenBegin - an identifying begin index for the token
        tokenEnd - an identifying end index for the token
        Returns:
        true if this token means that this class has seen a number in the tokens that have been passed to it, false otherwise.
